<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="319" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,582,787]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,284,582,607]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">Discussion.</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName box="[449,588,583,607]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Folsomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="14" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taimyrica">
<emphasis box="[449,588,583,607]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">F. taimyrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex (' 
<taxonomicName box="[719,877,582,606]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Folsomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="14" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrioculata">
<emphasis box="[719,877,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">quadrioculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
' group) which is defined by the combination of reduced ms formula (
<number box="[404,432,618,642]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319" value="10.0">10</number>
/ 
<number box="[441,484,618,642]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319" value="100.0">100</number>
) and the absence of ocelli and median macrochaetae on Th.III. Specimens from Buryatia have longer macrochaetae than in typical populations of 
<emphasis box="[889,991,655,679]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">F. v t o ro v i</emphasis>
(Central Asia).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="319" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,582,787]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,500,690,715]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
A rare species occurring in damp forests (
<figureCitation box="[979,1048,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,700,1864]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. The sampling sites in Buryatia: 1 – 2 — Vitim Plateau (1 — Konda Basin, 2 — Eravna Basin), 3 – 5 — Selenga Low Plateau (3 — Zagansky Range, 4 — vicinities of Schuch'ye Lake, 5 — vicinities of Karasinoye Lake), 6 – 8 — Barguzinsky Range (6 — Ust' - Barguzin, 7 — vicinities of Barguzin, 8 — upper flow of Barguzin River), 9 — Khamar-Daban Range, 10 — Tunkinskiye Gol'tsy Range, 11 — vicinities of Ulan-Ude, 12 — estuary of Selenga River, 13 — vicinities of Khorinsk, 14 — vicinities of Unnokent'evka, 15 –– Turka." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254496/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[1032,1048,690,714]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
: loc. 
<number box="[1108,1148,690,714]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319" value="1.4">1, 4</number>
). In Siberia the species is probably widely distributed, but contrasting ecological and morphological data indicate that several species are covered by the name 
<emphasis box="[390,492,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">F. v t oro v i</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
